body:
I just did this on my mac, using Mac CPU nightly from last week:

```
unset TF_CPP_MIN_LOG_LEVEL
export TF_CPP_MIN_VLOG_LEVEL=1
python -c "import tensorflow as tf; s = tf.Session(); s.run(tf.ones(()))"

```
and I saw a bunch of messages like this

```
2017-05-09 12:24:27.745962: I tensorflow/core/framework/log_memory.cc:35] __LOG_MEMORY__ MemoryLogTensorAllocation { step_id: -6 kernel_name: "Unknown (from Proto)" tensor { dtype: DT_FLOAT shape { } allocation_description { requested_bytes: 4 allocator_name: "cpu" ptr: 140654466064000 } } }
```
